30
00:03:46,580 --> 00:03:49,020
SPEAKER_23: Come often. You're always welcome.

33
00:04:50,449 --> 00:04:52,779
SPEAKER_23: Me and my lover

34
00:04:52,850 --> 00:04:55,220
SPEAKER_23: want more time

333
00:37:14,190 --> 00:37:17,820
SPEAKER_23: The coat's from my brother's unit.

449
00:52:47,659 --> 00:52:49,050
SPEAKER_23: It's ready.

456
00:53:07,340 --> 00:53:10,969
SPEAKER_23: We're racing towards Communism,
and you worry about food?

573
01:06:35,639 --> 01:06:38,269
SPEAKER_23: You little bastard! I'll break your legs!

575
01:07:47,960 --> 01:07:49,690
SPEAKER_23: We've smelted our steel...

576
01:07:49,760 --> 01:07:51,989
SPEAKER_23: and reached our production target.

577
01:07:52,059 --> 01:07:54,500
SPEAKER_23: We're off to report the good news.

578
01:07:55,230 --> 01:07:57,219
SPEAKER_23: Everyone's earned merit.

579
01:07:57,670 --> 01:08:01,969
SPEAKER_23: Fugui, Jiazhen,
you've made a real contribution.

580
01:08:02,610 --> 01:08:05,670
SPEAKER_23: There'll be dumplings
at the canteen tonight...

581
01:08:06,309 --> 01:08:09,239
SPEAKER_23: with a whole pig stuffed in each one!

582
01:08:12,050 --> 01:08:16,380
SPEAKER_23: Eat your fill, and then we'll continue.

583
01:08:16,720 --> 01:08:19,920
SPEAKER_23: Fifteen years, we'll surpass America.

584
01:08:27,100 --> 01:08:31,500
SPEAKER_23: We've made enough steel
for three cannon balls.

585
01:08:31,569 --> 01:08:33,590
SPEAKER_23: They'll all go to Taiwan!

586
01:08:34,800 --> 01:08:37,000
SPEAKER_23: One to land on Chiang Kai-shek's bed...

587
01:08:37,069 --> 01:08:39,340
SPEAKER_23: another on his dinner table...

588
01:08:39,409 --> 01:08:42,399
SPEAKER_23: and the last in the toilet!

589
01:08:44,449 --> 01:08:47,880
SPEAKER_23: He won't be able to sleep or eat
or ever take a dump...

590
01:08:48,520 --> 01:08:50,539
SPEAKER_23: and we'll liberate Taiwan!

704
01:21:12,090 --> 01:21:16,000
SPEAKER_23: What are you doing, you little wretch?
I'll teach you a lesson!

709
01:21:26,710 --> 01:21:28,470
SPEAKER_23: Who the heck is she?

710
01:21:29,310 --> 01:21:31,279
SPEAKER_23: Let her go!

764
01:26:32,479 --> 01:26:34,449
SPEAKER_23: Comrade Wan Erxi's here.

778
01:27:58,970 --> 01:28:00,869
SPEAKER_23: Comrade Wan Erxi.

841
01:33:42,880 --> 01:33:46,399
SPEAKER_23: Today comrades, Wan Erxi and Xu Fengxia...

842
01:33:46,819 --> 01:33:48,779
SPEAKER_23: begin their wedded life.

843
01:33:49,350 --> 01:33:52,720
SPEAKER_23: In good times, we think of Chairman Mao.

844
01:33:53,149 --> 01:33:54,819
SPEAKER_23: Let's sing a song!

861
01:36:01,180 --> 01:36:02,770
SPEAKER_23: Time to wrap up.

862
01:36:03,050 --> 01:36:05,579
SPEAKER_23: First, pay respects to Chairman Mao.

1029
01:50:01,420 --> 01:50:05,520
SPEAKER_23: Send her my very best. She's producing
a little revolutionary successor.

